pany’s global environmental sustainability strategy he is retiring on april     peiros was active in the work of aci for over  years he served on aci’s board of directors for  years as chair of the finance committee and treasurer from  contributing to aci’s strong financial position he further provided leadership serving on the board’s executive committee from    “larry peiros has been a tremendous asset to aci and to the cleaning products industry atlarge” said ernie rosenberg aci president  ceo “those of us on the staff who have worked with him directly have deep respect and affection   “a mere recitation of the positions he’s held does not capture how much of a contribution he has made and how important his leadership has been to the development of the institute and its staff  i am personally deeply grateful that i had the opportunity to work with and learn from larry” rosenberg added   “for decades aci has been at the forefront of promoting the benefits of cleaning products and protecting the ability of its members to formulate products that best meet consumer needs” said larry peiros “it has been exciting and personally fulfilling to be a part of this effort working with respected leaders from other member companies as well as a group of extremely capable professionals that make up the aci staff”   aci’s distinguished service award is named in honor of the late elva walker spillane the former national purity llc chief executive who served on the association’s board for  years   the award honors an individual for extensive or exceptional service to aci who promoted the growth and interests of the institute and the industries it represents and who exercised outstanding leadership within the institute     disclaimer please note that facebook comments are posted through facebook and cannot be approved edited or declined by cleanlinkcom the opinions expressed in facebook comments do not necessarily reflect those of cleanlinkcom or its staff to find out more about fa